# Frontend Safety — NBOS Web

You are working on **frontend UI only unless explicitly told otherwise.

## Allowed edit scope (SAFE_FRONTEND_EDIT_SCOPE)

You MAY edit files under:

- apps/web/src/features/**
- apps/web/src/components/**
- apps/web/src/app/(app)/** and apps/web/src/app/(auth)/** (pages/layouts only — NOT app/api/)
- apps/web/src/hooks/**
- apps/web/src/lib/format/**, lib/date/**, lib/utils.ts, lib/download-tabular-csv.ts, lib/persisted-client-state/**, lib/notifications/** (UI)
- apps/web/src/app/globals.css
- apps/web/public/**
- Co-located *.test.ts(x) under apps/web/

Before editing, state which files you plan to change and keep diffs minimal and frontend-scoped.

## Forbidden (DO_NOT_TOUCH_SCOPE)

Do NOT edit:

- apps/api/**
- packages/database/** (schema, migrations, seeds, generated client)
- packages/shared/** without explicit full-stack approval
- apps/web/src/auth.ts, apps/web/src/proxy.ts, apps/web/src/lib/bff-proxy.ts
- apps/web/src/app/api/**
- apps/web/next.config.ts (unless explicitly assigned)
- Root/monorepo: package.json, pnpm-lock.yaml, turbo.json, .github/**, Dockerfile.*, scripts/**
- .env, .env.local, apps/web/.env.local, or any secrets
- node_modules/**, .next/**, generated Prisma output

## Shared files — ask first

If a task requires changing:

- packages/shared/**
- apps/web/src/lib/api/** (REST paths/payload types)
- apps/web/src/lib/navigation/nav-config.ts
- apps/web/src/lib/permissions/**

Stop and ask for approval. Do not change API contracts or database schema.

## Workflow rules

1. Preserve existing architecture (features/, shared components, TanStack Query, persisted client state).
2. Do not run DB migrations or db:* scripts.
3. Do not change package versions or add dependencies without approval.
4. Do not remove files because knip or grep shows zero imports — flag for manual review instead.
5. Do not fix unrelated TypeScript/backend/CI errors outside apps/web unless explicitly asked.
6. Align behavior with docs/NBOS/05-UI-Specifications/** and relevant module canon (read-only unless docs task assigned).
7. No inline styles — Tailwind/classes only. No any. Named exports only.
8. Match existing patterns: PageHero, entity detail sheets, Kanban standards, permission gates.

## Product canon

docs/NBOS is source of truth for behavior. Do not invent UX from code alone when canon exists.
